01:10.468 --> 01:12.002
What about Ashley?

01:12.070 --> 01:14.004
I mean, shouldn't I tell him?

01:14.072 --> 01:15.973
Darling, in matters
of the heart,

01:16.041 --> 01:18.007
it's best
not to overthink things.

01:18.075 --> 01:20.309
That's your advice, mother,
with your track record?

01:20.377 --> 01:22.812
What chasm of doom
has she led you to

01:22.880 --> 01:24.914
by way of her tips on romance?

01:24.982 --> 01:26.515
As it happens,

01:26.584 --> 01:29.452
we were discussing
secret admirer etiquette.

01:29.519 --> 01:30.611
You have a secret admirer?

01:30.711 --> 01:33.724
I always thought it was silly,
but now I'm kind of intrigued.

01:33.824 --> 01:36.859
And there is no need
to tell Ashley.

01:36.927 --> 01:39.395
How exactly
does a secret admirer

01:39.463 --> 01:41.864
express his admiration?

01:41.932 --> 01:43.633
He left a note in my locker.

01:43.701 --> 01:45.568
"As you walked down the hall,

01:45.636 --> 01:48.904
"a shard of sunlight glanced off
your rope of flaxen hair

01:48.972 --> 01:51.907
and set it aglow,
and I was enchanted."

01:51.975 --> 01:54.076
Oh, that's so poetic.

01:54.143 --> 01:56.845
I figure the rope of flaxen hair
is my french braid,

01:56.913 --> 01:59.514
which I only wore after gym
class, which means he saw me

01:59.582 --> 02:02.550
in the hall on the first floor
between fourth and fifth period.

02:02.619 --> 02:03.932
- Wait a minute. What are you doing?
- Narrowing down suspects.

02:04.230 --> 02:07.570
No, you can't do that. No, you...
No, that'll ruin the secret.

02:07.802 --> 02:08.752
No, it's like a mystery novel.

02:08.852 --> 02:11.053
You don't just go
to the last page, do you?

02:11.120 --> 02:12.376
Yes.

02:12.576 --> 02:15.857
You do? Well, you shouldn't.
It's not... You can't...

02:17.694 --> 02:20.095
The... the joy doesn't come

02:20.163 --> 02:21.830
in knowing who did it.

02:21.897 --> 02:24.666
The joy comes in the journey,

02:24.734 --> 02:26.768
in allowing the ending
to blossom

02:26.836 --> 02:29.371
like some magnificent
Himalayan Blue Poppy,

02:29.439 --> 02:31.340
- like a...
- Okay.

02:31.407 --> 02:34.443
Okay.
I'll let him stay a secret.

02:34.511 --> 02:36.745
Mark my words.
You'll thank me.

02:36.812 --> 02:38.614
Mm.

02:40.016 --> 02:41.650
Castle.

02:41.717 --> 02:45.086
So our victim is Linda Russo.

02:45.155 --> 02:48.056
She's a customer relations
worker at a cable company.

02:48.124 --> 02:50.125
Maybe someone was unsatisfied
with their service.

02:50.192 --> 02:51.466
Yeah, that's what
I was thinking.

02:51.666 --> 02:52.866
You were?

02:53.328 --> 02:54.829
Oh.

02:54.897 --> 02:57.766
Sanitation workers found her
body under a couple of boxes.

02:57.833 --> 03:01.002
She lives 2 blocks away,
over at 24th and 10th.

03:01.070 --> 03:02.804
Looks like she was
on her way home.

03:02.872 --> 03:04.305
Hey, Lanie.

03:04.373 --> 03:06.007
Hey.

03:08.978 --> 03:10.578
What?

03:10.646 --> 03:12.080
Uh...

03:12.148 --> 03:13.581
It's nothing.

03:13.649 --> 03:15.483
No, what?

03:15.551 --> 03:18.252
Well, she just...
Looks so peaceful.

03:18.320 --> 03:20.789
There's nothing peaceful
about what put her here.

03:20.856 --> 03:23.523
- She was strangled.
- With rope?

03:23.591 --> 03:26.060
So it appears.

03:26.127 --> 03:27.545
Castle, do you have a theory

03:27.596 --> 03:29.068
that you would like to share
with the class?

03:29.168 --> 03:32.337
Well, I-I... It's just that,
pretty blonde girl, strangled,

03:32.671 --> 03:35.106
laid out like she was asleep.

03:35.174 --> 03:37.475
That was four years ago.

03:37.543 --> 03:40.941
Yes, but he was never caught.
This is his M.O.

03:41.041 --> 03:42.909
And she is certainly his type.

03:42.977 --> 03:45.330
I researched him for
"When it Comes to Slaughter."

03:45.430 --> 03:47.803
Yeah? Well, then you should know
that he killed his victims

03:47.903 --> 03:50.404
inside their apartments,
not in alleyways.

03:50.472 --> 03:51.560
And he posed them

03:51.639 --> 03:54.311
in a funereal pose with their
hands clasped in front of them.

03:55.409 --> 03:57.139
Maybe he's switching up
his act.

03:57.339 --> 03:59.165
Or this just could be
a crime of opportunity

03:59.265 --> 04:00.825
where a young woman
was murdered.

04:04.904 --> 04:06.805
Mrs. Russo, did your daughter
ever talk to you

04:06.873 --> 04:08.340
about being followed?

04:08.407 --> 04:10.308
No. Nothing like that.

04:10.376 --> 04:12.248
Can you think of anyone that
might have wanted to harm her?

04:12.348 --> 04:13.622
Any relationship problems?

04:13.822 --> 04:15.066
She wasn't even dating.

04:16.093 --> 04:17.642
Pretty much
all she did was work.

04:17.743 --> 04:19.644
- At the, uh, cable company, right?
- Mm-hmm.

04:19.711 --> 04:22.280
Did she have any issues
with anyone there?

04:22.348 --> 04:24.714
Uh... there was
a man at her office.

04:24.782 --> 04:26.984
- What was his name?
- She didn't say.

04:27.052 --> 04:30.154
But he stared at her a lot,
like some pervert.

04:37.028 --> 04:39.296
- That was quick.
- 9-1-1 has that affect on her.

04:39.364 --> 04:40.554
What'd you find?

04:40.566 --> 04:43.731
I pulled all the files on all his
past murders, just like you asked.

04:43.734 --> 04:45.735
I-I believe
that was my idea.

04:45.803 --> 04:48.038
Yeah, but I only listen
when it comes from her.

04:48.106 --> 04:49.974
Anyway, you were saying?

04:50.041 --> 04:51.575
He choked them using

04:51.642 --> 04:53.510
a 3-strand, twisted
quarter-inch rope.

04:53.578 --> 04:56.012
Based on the fibers found
embedded in the skin,

04:56.080 --> 04:58.781
we know that the rope
is green and white nylon.

04:58.849 --> 05:01.351
I don't remember that.

05:01.418 --> 05:03.219
Those details
were never made public.

05:03.287 --> 05:05.754
Now check this out.

05:08.492 --> 05:10.193
The marks are identical.

05:10.260 --> 05:13.496
I found the exact same
green and white fibers.

05:13.563 --> 05:15.731
It is him.

05:15.799 --> 05:17.800
The triple killer is back.

05:17.868 --> 05:20.736
For those of you
living in a cave four years ago,

05:20.804 --> 05:22.905
the triple killer, or 3xk,

05:22.973 --> 05:25.140
got his nickname by strangling
three women in a week,

05:25.208 --> 05:27.142
dropping out of sight
for a month,

05:27.210 --> 05:29.044
and then killing three more,
then he disappeared.

05:29.112 --> 05:31.146
I served on the task force

05:31.214 --> 05:33.382
that investigated
those six murders.

05:33.449 --> 05:36.485
An FBI profile was as close as
we came to I.D.'ing a suspect.

05:36.552 --> 05:40.555
- The Feds say he's a white male,
25 to 45 years old...- Could be me.

05:40.756 --> 05:42.724
- With a dysfunctional relationship
with his mother. - Still me.

05:42.925 --> 05:44.739
He has a menial,
unimportant job.

05:44.839 --> 05:46.029
Definitely you.

05:46.329 --> 05:49.297
Just for that, I base my next book
on Esposito. He'd learn their habits,

05:49.365 --> 05:51.299
and then gain access
to their apartments

05:51.367 --> 05:53.268
by disguising himself
as a security guard

05:53.336 --> 05:56.170
or a repairman,
and then he strangled 'em.

05:56.238 --> 05:59.153
Then he posed their bodies as if
they were lying in a coffin.

06:00.008 --> 06:01.797
What do you think
that's all about?

06:01.811 --> 06:04.230
Probably reenacting
some terrible early trauma.

06:04.330 --> 06:05.078
Hmm.

06:05.100 --> 06:07.168
Two final points...
The triple killer

06:07.236 --> 06:09.103
seems to be back
after four years.

06:09.171 --> 06:11.906
There must be a reason.
Maybe he just got out of prison

06:11.974 --> 06:14.108
or returned to town.
He may have altered his M.O.

06:14.176 --> 06:17.579
But let's assume that he's
working under the same clock...

06:17.646 --> 06:19.347
Three murders, one week.

06:19.415 --> 06:21.315
Based on Linda Russo's
time of death,

06:21.384 --> 06:23.418
we're already into day three.

06:23.486 --> 06:25.058
Let's move on this, people.

06:27.122 --> 06:30.090
Hey. That perv the mom
told us about?

06:30.157 --> 06:32.025
Linda's colleagues knew
who he was right away.

06:32.093 --> 06:33.694
Paul McCardle.

06:33.762 --> 06:35.248
He works at her office
as a horticultural technician.

06:35.348 --> 06:36.748
A what?

06:36.898 --> 06:39.165
Uh, you know, he's the guy
who waters the plants,

06:39.233 --> 06:41.067
dusts the fake ficus,
or at least he was

06:41.135 --> 06:42.703
until he quit yesterday.

06:42.771 --> 06:43.966
That's interesting timing.

06:44.039 --> 06:46.549
I see domestic complaints
by the double digits.

06:46.649 --> 06:47.608
Filed by his wife.

06:47.709 --> 06:49.510
Ex-wife. They were
divorced last month

06:49.577 --> 06:51.311
after being married
for four years.

06:51.379 --> 06:53.445
So in a way, he did
just get out of prison.

06:53.645 --> 06:54.415
It gets even better.

06:54.416 --> 06:56.583
Linda's neighbors said
they remember seeing

06:56.651 --> 06:59.119
a red Sentra parked outside
her apartment a few days ago...

06:59.186 --> 07:00.155
The same vehicle McCardle has.

07:00.355 --> 07:01.555
Let's get him in here.

07:02.589 --> 07:05.025
So what's this about?
Linda Russo.

07:05.092 --> 07:07.827
Where were you 2 nights ago
between 6:00 and midnight?

07:07.895 --> 07:11.531
Ome
buddies at, uh, Galaxy Lanes.

07:11.598 --> 07:13.566
So why did you decide
to abandon your career

07:13.634 --> 07:14.893
as a horticultural technician?

07:14.993 --> 07:16.193
I-I just wanted to move on.

07:16.503 --> 07:19.339
Because you used that job
to watch Linda, to stalk her.

07:19.407 --> 07:21.374
And once she was dead,
why stick around?

07:21.442 --> 07:23.509
That is not true.
I'm innocent here.

07:23.577 --> 07:25.478
Well, you don't look innocent.

07:25.546 --> 07:27.547
No, as a matter of fact,
you give new meaning

07:27.614 --> 07:29.549
to the phrase
"sweating a suspect."

07:29.616 --> 07:31.201
Okay, yeah,
I perspire a lot, okay?

07:31.218 --> 07:32.958
I have a medical condition.

07:33.058 --> 07:35.577
Well, that's the least of
your problems, Mr. McCardle.

07:35.755 --> 07:38.557
Your fixation with Linda Russo
was well known,

07:38.624 --> 07:40.559
as was your history
of violence against women.

07:40.626 --> 07:42.494
Your car was seen
outside of her apartment,

07:42.562 --> 07:44.229
and now she's dead.

07:44.297 --> 07:47.099
I never touched her.

07:47.167 --> 07:49.468
I had a thing for Linda, okay.
I had a thing for Linda,

07:49.535 --> 07:51.026
and I parked
out in front of her place.

07:51.072 --> 07:53.745
But I haven't been anywhere
near there in three days, okay?

07:53.845 --> 07:55.336
Not since
that guy threatened me.

07:55.436 --> 07:56.534
What guy?

07:56.949 --> 07:58.884
I-I got... I got rousted
by some security guy,

07:58.951 --> 08:02.186
and... and he told me to move on.
And it really freaked me out,

08:02.254 --> 08:04.055
and I haven't
been back there since.

08:04.123 --> 08:06.457
I swear. That's the truth.

08:06.525 --> 08:10.189
So sweaty Von sweats-a-lot?
His alibi is holding.

08:10.289 --> 08:12.567
The manager of Galaxy Lanes
has him throwing gutter balls

08:12.658 --> 08:13.883
from 5:00 until close.

08:13.983 --> 08:15.183
What about the security guard?

08:15.360 --> 08:17.295
Ryan checked into that.
Turns out that there's

08:17.362 --> 08:19.297
only one building on
Linda's block that uses guards.

08:19.364 --> 08:20.799
According to
the security company,

08:20.866 --> 08:22.733
no incident report
was ever filed

08:22.802 --> 08:23.799
against McCardle
or his vehicle.

08:23.999 --> 08:24.969
So McCardle was lying.

08:26.104 --> 08:28.139
Maybe not.
You know, in the past,

08:28.239 --> 08:30.173
the triple killer
posed as a security guard.

08:30.241 --> 08:32.140
Maybe our guard
wasn't a guard after all.

08:32.207 --> 08:35.644
Maybe it was the triple killer
moving McCardle off of his turf.

08:35.711 --> 08:38.948
Well, whoever he is,
he's sticking to his schedule.

08:39.015 --> 08:40.448
We have a second victim.

08:42.217 --> 08:45.620
